I know that this will just get lost in the hundreds and hundreds of comments here. But I'm actually really down today. I'm alone at my house, and my parents are in the hospital. I can't be with them because of COVID protocols and I still need to work (adulting problems).

But thanks to TWICE and this episode. I suddenly feel warm. Like I'm no longer alone anymore. I hope that one day, you'll get to read this and know how much you've made someone else's day a lot better. :)

Thank you.

author: @vahl1471
text:
I don't know how it happened but I started liking Twice as people before I had listened to any of their music. As an ult InSomnia I was pretty sure I couldn't like Twice's music, it was so much the opposite of what I'm into. At first I couldn't stand it, made it through like the first 3 title tracks and stopped. I knew it was well made and they were extremely talented musicians but I didn't think I'd ever like it. So I watched a ton of their non-music content and fell head over heels in love with them as people and entertainers. I was like "Can I be a Once if I don't really like their music?" 

I wanted so much to enjoy their music so I tried again. I started with Between 1&2 this time, loved TTT, and went backward from there. Once I got used their sound and how different it was from DeuKae I started to really vibe with it and they are now my second most listened to group!! I have an entire playlist called Duality and it's all Dreamcatcher and Twice. I listen to it every day at work 😂🤣 

That whole long story was to say how excited I am that now when I watch TTT and I hear their music in the background, I know the songs and jam out to them like all the other Onces!!!!!!  Also side note Like Ooh-Aah is legit one of my favorite songs now! 😉
